==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Figment
<hw>Fig"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>figmentum</ets>, fr. <ets>fingere</ets> to form, shape, invent,
feign. See <er>Feign</er>.]</ety> <def>An invention; a fiction;
something feigned or imagined.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Social <qex>figments</qex>, feints, and formalism.</q>
<rj><qau>Mrs. Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It carried rather an appearance of <qex>figment</qex> and
invention . . . than of truth and reality.</q>
<rj><qau>Woodward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Figpecker</ent>⟦br⟧
